Google Image Search is an excellent source of traffic these days, though it's much harder to target. The best you can usually do is upload a unique image, add very descriptive alt text and keywords, and hope it ranks well. A stock photo, though? Not only is your version not the only version, but two dozen stock photo websites will also have it visible, and there's a pretty good chance that they'll all outrank you.

ever read content on news sites or a site like Cracked, you'll see attribution beneath every image. "Image © The Associated Press" or "Image from Getty Images" or what have you.
